pageContext.claim: “Did you see they did a New York Times poll? I think in Siena, New York Times of Iowa, and they have me pitted against every one of the socialists and we're winning by a lot, everyone. We're beating them all.”
pageContext.analysis: Trump was in a statistical neck-and-neck with Pete Buttigieg and Joe Biden in the poll from Siena College and the New York Times, leading them by 1 and 2 points in Iowa, respectively. In fact, the Iowa poll showed Trump narrowly leading several of the top Democratic contenders, after winning the state by 9 percentage points in 2016.
